'''Paul Michael Junior Okon-Engstler''' ({{IPA|vls|ˈoːkɔn ˈɛŋstlər|lang}}: born 24 January 2005), also known as '''Paul Okon Junior''',{{efn|"Junior" can be shortened to "Jnr" (as used on his [[Sydney FC]] jersey)<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://sydneyfc.com/player/paul-okon/|title=Paul Okon Jnr|publisher=[[Sydney FC]]}}</ref> or "Jr".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8889671/okon-jr-ready-to-follow-path-blazed-by-his-father/|title=Okon Jr ready to follow path blazed by his father|first=George|last=Clarke|publisher=[[The Canberra Times]]|date=11 February 2025}}</ref>}} is a professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Sydney FC]] in the [[A-League Men]]. Born in Belgium, he represents the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]].

==Club career==
Born in Belgium while his father, former Australian international soccer player [[Paul Okon]] was playing for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[K.V. Oostende]], Okon-Engstler moved to Australia in 2006 when his father signed for the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].<ref name=tm>{{cite web|url=https://teknomers.com/es/paul-okon-engstler-el-talento-australiano-del-benfica-lleva-una-vida-loca-como-un-padre/|title=Paul Okon-Engstler: el talento australiano del Benfica lleva una vida loca como un padre|trans-title=Paul Okon-Engstler: Benfica's Australian talent leads a crazy life like a father|date=20 December 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=teknomers.com|language=Spanish}}</ref> He started his career, as his father had, with [[Marconi Stallions FC|Marconi Stallions]], before moving to [[A-League Men|A-League]] side [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]].<ref name=tm/> In 2019, he moved back to Belgium, signing with [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].<ref name=tm/>

While representing Club Brugge at a youth tournament in Portugal, he was spotted by scouts from [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], despite Club Brugge's poor performances at the tournament.<ref name=optus>{{cite web|url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/socceroos/os45041/football-news-socceroos-paul-okon-junior-benfica-transfer-details|title=Paul Okon Junior joins Portuguese giants Benfica|first=Jake|last=Rosengarten|date=20 July 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=sport.optus.com.au}}</ref> He joined the Portuguese club in July 2022, signing a three-year deal.<ref name=optus/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2022/07/19/futebol-benfica-formacao-paul-okon-contratacao|title=Paul Okon contratado|trans-title=Paul Okon hired|date=19 July 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=slbenfica.pt|language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20220720_92317742|title=Zoon van assistent Paul Okon verlaat Club Brugge voor Benfica|trans-title=Son of assistant Paul Okon leaves Club Brugge for Benfica|first=Martin|last=Delvaux|date=20 July 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=nieuwsblad.be|language=Dutch}}</ref>

In July 2025, Okon-Engstler signed for [[A-League Men]] side [[Sydney FC]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sydneyfc.com/news/sydney-fc-lands-socceroos-young-gun-paul-okon-engstler/|title=Sydney FC lands Socceroos Young Gun Paul Okon-Engstler|website=[[Sydney FC]]|date=25 July 2025}}</ref> His debut for the club came against [[Western United FC|Western United]] in the opening round of the [[2025 Australia Cup]].

==International career==
Okon-Engstler is eligible to represent Belgium through birth, Australia through his father, and Italy through his mother.<ref name=tm/> He holds Italian citizenship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/italiano-okon-engstler-reforca-equipa-sub-19-do-benfica-clube-lindo-e-historico|title=Italiano Okon-Engstler reforça equipa sub-19 do Benfica: "Clube lindo e histórico"|trans-title=Italian Okon-Engstler reinforces Benfica's under-19 team: «Beautiful and historic club»|date=19 July 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=record.pt|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

In September 2022, he was called up to the [[Australia men's national under-20 soccer team|Australia under-20 team]], but did not feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/young-socceroos-squad-named-four-continents-tournament-spain|title=Young Socceroos Squad Named for Four Continents Tournament in Spain|date=13 September 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=socceroos.com.au}}</ref>

He made his debut for the [[Australia men's national under-23 soccer team|Australia under-23 team]] during the [[2023 Maurice Revello Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/olyroos-squad-named-maurice-revello-tournament|title=Olyroos squad named for Maurice Revello Tournament|website=[[Australia men's national soccer team|Socceroos]]|publisher=[[Football Australia]]|date=15 May 2023}}</ref>

In June 2025, Okon was called up for the [[Socceroos]] squad for qualifiers against Japan and Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{cite web | title=Son of gun: Okon Jr. Earns Socceroos call-up | date=June 2025 | url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/45414533/son-gun-paul-okon-engstler-earns-socceroos-call-up }}</ref>

==Style of play==
A composed, left-footed [[defensive midfielder]], Okon-Engstler is known for his range of long passes, and is capable of starting attacks from deep.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/08/10/paul-okon-jr-following-in-famous-fathers-footsteps/|title=Paul Okon Jr following in famous father's footsteps|date=9 August 2022|accessdate=6 March 2023|website=theroar.com.au}}</ref>

